
[1]sardonic

   SARDON'IC, a. Sardonian or sardonic laughter, a convulsive involuntary
   laughter, so called from the herba sardonia, a species of ranunculus,
   which is said to produce such convulsive motions in the cheeks and lips
   as are observed during a fit of laughter.

   SARDON'IC, a. Denoting a kind of linen made at Colchis.
